<title> Karyus <>

<section> Introduction <>
    <p>The world of Karyus is filled with arcane magic and mechanical wonders. The origins of the world are somewhat
    unclear and history has not been recorded for that long a time.<>
    <p>Everything in Karyus revolves around mana particles. These are everpresent particles in all existing matter. They
    can be harvested and used as a resource to do many things.<>
    <p>Many different creatures inhabit Karyus, emcopassing many different sentient races. The most common races include
    <a t="races_humans">Humans<>, <a t="races_cirrans">Cirrans<>, foo and bar.<>

<section> History <>
    <p>Different civilizations have different records, but most people don't know much about what happened more than
    around 3700 years ago, where a terrible disaster destroyed much of known civilization. Archaeological ruins
    exists from before this time, but are hard to find, and often quite dangerous.<>
    <heading level="1"> The Apocalypse of Karthuun <>
        <p>The most ancient stories and records tell of a devasting war which nearly destroyed several kingdoms and
        empires. All of the kingdoms in the south of <a t="places_cariadon">Cariadon<> allied together to fight of a
        horde from the North called the <a t="places_kjeldorn">Kjeldorn<>.<>
        <p>The details of this war remain mostly unknown, but one of the thing we do know is that we paid a great price
        to win the war. The next few hundred years came to be known as the Black Years by all around.<>
    <heading level="1"> The Black Years <>
        <p>The Black Years were a period of recovery for all the Southern kingdoms as they stuggled to regain their
        former glory.<>

